content: Yes, members of the British Royal Family are subject to the same travel regulations as other UK citizens and are required to hold valid passports for international travel. However, the process of obtaining a passport for a member of the royal family is handled differently than for ordinary citizens. The Passport Office works with the royal household to issue passports, and the process is not made public. Additionally, some members of the royal family may hold diplomatic passports, which offer additional privileges and immunities while traveling on official business.
